# Cloudflare Workers Static Assets exclusion list.
# When workers builds run `wrangler deploy`, it treats the entire
# repository root as the assets directory (per wrangler.jsonc's
# `assets.directory: "."`). We need to exclude non-public files
# to keep the deploy bundle under 25 MiB.
#
# Without this, the `.git/objects/pack/*.pack` files (often >25 MiB)
# blow past the Workers 25 MiB total asset limit and fail with:
#   [ERROR] Asset too large. ... We found a file .../.git/...
#      with a size of 27.4 MiB.
#
# 06-24 13:47 log: wrangler tried to bundle .git/pack-d2a5....pack
# (27.4 MiB) and aborted the entire deploy. So the latest commit
# WAS deployed to CF, but the deploy *job* failed mid-bundle, leaving
# CF serving stale state from before this run.

# Version control
.git/
.gitignore
.gitattributes

# Editor / OS noise
.DS_Store
*.swp
*.swo
*~
.idea/
.vscode/

# Build artefacts of the wrapper repo itself (this is just a deploy
# repo — there are no source files to build, all assets are pre-built)
node_modules/
**/node_modules/
package-lock.json
yarn.lock
pnpm-lock.yaml

# 06-27: neo-labs-build/ is the Next.js SOURCE for /neo-labs/ deploy
# (build output goes to neo-labs/, not neo-labs-build/). neo-labs-build/
# holds 666 MB of source code + node_modules with 134 MB swc binaries
# that crash the 25 MiB Workers asset limit.
neo-labs-build/

# 06-27: agentic-3d-mvp/ is untracked local development scratch with
# 72 MB of Swift toolchain binaries (.pcm files) — not part of deploy.
agentic-3d-mvp/

# 06-27: .github/ contains local workflow files (cf-pages-deploy.yml is
# the original GH Action config but deploy actually runs via CF Workers
# GitHub App, not this workflow).
.github/

# Python tooling
__pycache__/
*.pyc
.venv/

# Deploy-time scratch files we created to force-rebuild (06-24)
.deploy-trigger
.deploy-marker

# Anything specifically labelled as not-public
**/.env
**/.env.*
**/secrets.json
